  "prompt": "How long HCL technology takes to give offer letter after document uploading round for experience?",
  "response": "The timeline for receiving an offer letter from **HCL Technologies** after the document uploading round for experienced candidates can vary. Typically, the process takes **1 to 3 weeks**, depending on factors like:\n\n1. **Background Verification**: For experienced candidates, the verification process (employment history, education, etc.) can take time.\n2. **Internal Approvals**: HCL may require internal approvals before issuing the offer letter.\n3. **Role and Location**: The complexity of the role and the location can also impact the timeline.\n4. **Volume of Applications**: If there is a high volume of applications, the process might take longer.\n\nIf it\u2019s been more than 3 weeks, consider reaching out to the HR contact or recruiter for an update. They can provide specific details about the status of your application.",
